Latest stable and nightly rustc hangs and quits with "out of memory" error on this code:
```rust
pub struct A;
pub struct B {
  pub a: Vec<A>,
  pub b: Vec<B>,
}

impl B {
  pub fn f1<F>(&self, f: F)
    where F: Fn(&A) -> bool
  {
    self.a.iter().find(|x| f(x));
    for b in &self.b {
      b.f1(|x| f(x));
    }
  }
}

fn main() {
  let x = B {
    a: Vec::new(),
    b: Vec::new(),
  };
  x.f1(|_| true);
}
```

If I change order of lines to this:
```rust
    for b in &self.b {
      b.f1(|x| f(x));
    }
    self.a.iter().find(|x| f(x));
```
